According to Angus Mackay:
> I really think that 31bit files are quite limiting(ext2).
Ext2 handles huge files just fine.  On the other hand, getting huge
files to work with the VM of 32-bit CPUs (e.g. the i386) is more
difficult; experimental patches exist (as has been noted already).
